### Create user group

#### Parameters

| Field | Type | Location | Required | Description |
|--|--|--|--|--|--|--|
| system_id | string | path | Yes | Access to system unique identifier |
| grade_manager_id | int or "-" | path | Yes | The grade administrator ID, `for which grade_manager_id is not provided in the URL (the value is a horizontal bar "-"), it means that the user group is created under the system administrator corresponding to {system_id}` |
| groups | array | body | yes | list of user groups to be created |

groups

| field | type | whether required | location | description |
| --------|--------|--------|--------|--------|--------|--------|
| name | string | yes | body | User group name, at least 5 characters, unique under the same hierarchical administrator |
| description | string | yes | body | User group description, at least 10 characters |
| readonly | bool | no | body | Optional parameter, default is false, user group is read-only |

Description.

The user group created with readonly: True can only be managed through the admin api, the user group can only be viewed on the permission center SaaS, but cannot be managed, such as: add permission/add member/delete

#### Request

```json
{
  "groups": [
    {
      "name": "test1".
      "description": "test1test1"
    }.
    {
      "name": "test2".
      "description": "test1test2".
      "readonly": true
    }.
  ]
}
```

